  <div class='frost-modal-demo-notes'>
    <p>
      Because sometimes you need to make an entrance <i>(or exit)</i>
    </p>
    <p>
      Along with basic modal primitives <b>\{{frost-modal-binding}}</b> provides an option to animate
      the visibility of a modal.  Because we care the animation is configurable on a per-modal basis
      and because it's awesome the animations are managed using the
      <a href='http://ember-animation.github.io/liquid-fire/#/transitions/explode'>Liquid Fire</a>
      transition language.
    </p>
    <p>
      Animation transitions are functions provided by a helper or a local function; a few predefined
      animations are avaiable via the <b>frost-modal-animation</b> helper and are intended to be paired
      with the predefined modal components available in this addon.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class='frost-modal-demo-title'>
